  "text": "Worm fecundity is strongly correlated with the size of the worm; at the same time, worm size depends on the strength of the IgA response (specifically, IgA m ) and a density-dependent effect of the number of worms in the animal [CITATION_1] . Worm number and worm fecundity determine the egg deposition onto pasture and subsequently the number of infective L3 larvae available to be ingested.",
